@disney__tasthic @ServalSketch It's all manageable Shelby. Depression/anxiety loves the routine-- you need to take the action and trick it!
@disney__tasthic The delusion is we can fix it by ourselves. I would speak to a professional whom you trust
column4: & let them help you solve this.

text: @disney__tasthic The long term affect of psychotropic meds can do exactly that. I think the time may have come for you to face it head on.

column4: but you need to do the work. Medication only temporarily numbs the feeling-- it won't make it go away.

text: @disney__tasthic That's called a "geographic" and moving won't solve things. You need to be brave and get to the cause of the anxiety.
@disney__tasthic You need to find what's at the source of these feelings if you want to overcome them. And that's scary to a lot of people.

column4: a group and/or counseling will do you a world of good❤️

text: @disney__tasthic My advice is find an affordable counselor or support group that you like and be very honest.

column4: speaking with a professional or a fellow sufferer  is what cures depression/anxiety.
